The disappearance of Kris Kremers and Lisanne Froon, two Dutch college graduates, have long fascinated the public. In 2014, after their graduation, the two went on a backpacking trip.  When they arrived in Panama, they stayed with a host family in Boquete. While there, they went hiking up the "Pianista" trail - one that was relatively challenging but not too difficult for young, healthy people such as themselves. They shouldn't have had any problems on that hike as long as they stayed on the trail going to the summit and back. 
Unfortunately, the girls never made it back. After an extensive search, authorities were only able to locate some of their belongings and parts of their bodies. And this was months after the girls had disappeared. 
Because of this, their cause of death could not be determined. The official explanation of the authorities was accidental death. Most people believe that the girls had gone off the trail and gotten lost. They were inexperienced and didn't know what to do. Phone records show that there were multiple attempts to call the Dutch emergency number. Unfortunately, no calls could be completed due to a lack of reception. It was also reported that both phones were turned on and off between calls. It was presumed that they were trying to conserve battery. Over time, the two women might have gotten wounded and then died due to exposure, thirst, hunger, or even attacks by animals. 
Though this was the official conclusion of law enforcement, many believe that the cause of the girls' disappearance and eventual death were far more sinister. In this video, we'll take a look at the wildest theories on Reddit about Kris Kremers and Lisanne Froon's disappearance and any evidence that may support them.
